The Newspapers and Magazines Distributors’ Association of Nigeria (NDAN) has announced the death of one of its members, Christian Chukwunenye Nwakaudu. The Chairman of the Lagos Island zone of NDAN, Godwin Akpan, announced that Nwakaudu died on January 1, 2020 at the age of 54. Nwakaudu, who hailed from Umuezike in Mgbidi Oru West Local Government Area, Imo State, will be buried on February 14, 2020 at Mgbidi.  Daily Trust''s appreciation of Newspaper vendors and agents in Lagos Newspaper vendors in Rivers threaten strike over harassment Wike sacks Rivers’ Accountant General